    "text": "The INPUT above shows how to use the 'title' and 'subtitle' areas to provide information to the players. You can also use the css background-color property to change the color of the input rows. Number fields with min-max values will automatically show the range."
  },
  "text2": {
    "id": "text2",
    "x": 325,
    "y": 430,
    "width": 300,
    "z": 121,
    "movable": false,
    "movableInEdit": false,
    "css": "font-size: 22px; ",
    "text": "The INPUT above shows how to use css to color the 'title' and 'subtitle' areas. The input box area will automatically adjust height and width to fit the content. You can also use variables in the 'value' parameter to pre-fill in data."
  },
  "text3": {
    "id": "text3",
    "x": 651,
    "y": 430,
    "width": 300,
    "z": 9732,
    "movable": false,
    "movableInEdit": false,
    "css": "font-size: 22px; ",
    "text": "This button shows how you can change the default 'Go' and 'Cancel' buttons to other text or icons. The icons must be from the VTT-Symbols list. See the wiki entry on Fonts for a list of names that can be used."
  },
  "text4": {
    "id": "text4",
    "x": 964,
    "y": 430,
    "width": 300,
    "z": 9732,
    "movable": false,
    "movableInEdit": false,
    "css": "font-size: 22px; ",
    "text": "This button shows how you can remove the option for a Cancel button. This will force players to continue with the selection and not give them a chance to return to the game without confirming."
  },
  "text5": {
    "id": "text5",
